A '''map surround''' is any of the supporting objects or elements that help a reader interpret a map. Typical map surround elements include the title, [[Legend (map)|legend]], north arrow, [[Linear scale|scale bar]], border, source information and other text, and inset maps.<ref>Wade, T. and Sommer, S. eds. ''[http://store.esri.com/esri/showdetl.cfm?SID=2&Product_ID=868&Category_ID=49 A to Z GIS]''</ref>
